Summary I have many and wide-ranging experiences in technology development and testing, much of it in communications & networks, that have provided a broad base for successfully managing software programs. Successful programs require a strong understanding of the customers' needs (requirements) and evaluating the program's teams in order to establish processes that allow the team to be successful in delivering the products. No two programs are the same. I continue to learn new technologies to be more effective in helping the development teams, as well as new program methodologies such as Agile, Scrum and Kanban to improve efficiency and productivity. However, fundamental program management methods of meeting the customer's needs (schedule, cost, quality), empowering highly effective teams and monitoring/reporting progress are at the heart of every successful program. Summary I have many and wide-ranging experiences in technology development and testing, much of it in communications & networks, that have provided a broad base for successfully managing software programs. Successful programs require a strong understanding of the customers' needs (requirements) and evaluating the program's teams in order to establish processes that allow the team to be successful in delivering the products. No two programs are the same. I continue to learn new technologies to be more effective in helping the development teams, as well as new program methodologies such as Agile, Scrum and Kanban to improve efficiency and productivity. However, fundamental program management methods of meeting the customer's needs (schedule, cost, quality), empowering highly effective teams and monitoring/reporting progress are at the heart of every successful program. I have many and wide-ranging experiences in technology development and testing, much of it in communications & networks, that have provided a broad base for successfully managing software programs. Successful programs require a strong under